# Plan: EdTech School Connect Web Portal
slug: edtech-school-connect-web-portal
feature richness: 10/10

---

## 1. Demo Concept

**"SchoolConnect" - A two-role parent-teacher communication and performance tracking portal**

A working, full-featured portal serving two distinct user roles: parents and teachers. The demo is seeded with one student ("Alex Johnson"), one parent account, and one teacher account. Both sides of every interaction are demoable by switching logins.

The demo lives at: `https://michaelwegter.com/demos/edtech-school-connect-web-portal/`

---

## 2. Prototype vs Full Decision

**Decision: FULL**

None of the fallback triggers are tripped:
1. Backend integration IS achievable cheaply via a new Flask blueprint on mw-backend.
2. Scope fits within caps: ~12 demo files, ~10 blueprint endpoints, builds in under 3 minutes.
3. This is not a visual-only concept -- real messaging, real grade updates, and real persistence are the core value proposition.

At richness 10/10, this is a production-quality MVP with multiple genuinely working features. Not a prototype with placeholders.

---

## 3. Architecture

### Frontend (static demo)
- **Location:** `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/edtech-school-connect-web-portal/`
- **Stack:** Vanilla JS + CDN-loaded Chart.js (no bundler -- self-contained)
- **Routing:** Single-page app with hash-based view switching
- **Auth:** JWT stored in localStorage; fetched from backend at login

### Backend
- **Location:** `../mw-backend/edtech_blueprint.py`
- **Register in:** `../mw-backend/server.py` (add `register_blueprint` call, no other changes)
- **Storage:** New prefixed tables in the existing `data/mw.db` SQLite database
- **Real-time:** Client-side polling every 4 seconds for messages and activity feed; genuinely live

### Demo Seeded Accounts
| Role    | Email              | Password    |
|---------|--------------------|-------------|
| Parent  | parent@demo.edu    | ParentDemo1 |
| Teacher | teacher@demo.edu   | TeachDemo1  |

Student: **Alex Johnson**, Grade 7

