## 5. Features (Hero + 2 Supporting + Polish)

### Hero Feature: Real-Time Parent-Teacher Messaging

**Description:** A threaded messaging system between parent and teacher. Both roles can compose and reply. Messages poll from the Flask backend every 4 seconds, so a message sent in the Teacher view appears in the Parent view without a refresh. Unread badge on the inbox nav icon. Message timestamps, read status, and sender name shown.

**Parent experience:**
- Inbox shows thread with Alex's teacher (Mrs. Rivera)
- "New Message" compose button
- Thread view with sent/received bubbles
- Read receipts (checkmark icon)
- Unread count badge on nav

**Teacher experience:**
- Inbox shows all parent threads (one in demo: Alex Johnson's parent)
- Compose and reply
- "Mark as read" auto-fires when thread is opened
- Timestamps

**Backend endpoints:**
- `POST /api/edtech/login` -- auth, returns JWT with `{ role, name, studentId }`
- `GET /api/edtech/messages` -- list threads (JWT-gated, role-aware)
- `POST /api/edtech/messages` -- send a new message
- `PATCH /api/edtech/messages/<id>/read` -- mark read
- `GET /api/edtech/messages/unread-count` -- badge count for polling

### Supporting Feature 1: Student Performance Dashboard

**Description:** A visual gradebook showing Alex Johnson's current grades across six subjects, plus a radar chart (Chart.js CDN) showing the performance profile, a calculated GPA, and a recent-grade-changes timeline. Teacher can update a grade inline (click subject card, type new grade, save). Parent sees the update within seconds (polling).

**Parent experience:**
- "Performance" nav section
- Quick stats bar at top: GPA, Grade Level, Attendance %
- Six subject cards (Math, English, Science, History, Art, PE) with current letter grade + numeric score + color-coded status (A=green, B=blue, C=yellow, D/F=red)
- Radar chart showing 6-axis performance profile
- "Recent Updates" mini-feed (last 5 grade changes with timestamp and subject)

**Teacher experience:**
- Same performance section but with edit controls
- Click any subject card to open an inline edit form
- Submit new grade (letter + numeric) -- saves to backend, appears on parent side via poll
- "Post Grade Update" also triggers an automatic activity feed entry

**Backend endpoints:**
- `GET /api/edtech/performance` -- returns grades JSON for seeded student
- `POST /api/edtech/performance` -- teacher updates a subject grade (JWT + role=teacher required)

### Supporting Feature 2: Activity and Announcements Feed

**Description:** A chronological feed of school events, academic milestones, attendance records, and announcements. Teacher can post new announcements from a compose form. Parent sees all feed items, newest first, with category badges.

**Parent experience:**
- "Activity Feed" nav section
- Chronological card list with category badge (Academic, Event, Attendance, Announcement)
- Rich feed: seeded items include grade milestone, upcoming science fair, attendance note, field trip announcement
- Pull-to-refresh (click "Refresh" button -- re-polls)
- Activity cards show icon, category color, teacher name, timestamp, body text

**Teacher experience:**
- Same feed view but with a "Post Announcement" sticky compose panel at top
- Title + body + category dropdown
- Submit fires `POST /api/edtech/activities` and the new item appears at top of both views

**Backend endpoints:**
- `GET /api/edtech/activities` -- list all activities, newest first
- `POST /api/edtech/activities` -- teacher creates a new announcement (JWT + role=teacher required)

### Polish Layer (Richness 10)

These additional details elevate the demo from "solid" to "production-quality":

1. **Role switcher on login screen:** Two big login tiles ("Log in as Parent" / "Log in as Teacher") that pre-fill the email/password so reviewers can instantly switch roles
2. **Notification badge system:** Unread message count shown in nav and in the page header
3. **Attendance mini-widget:** In the parent dashboard overview, a small attendance card shows "Alex: 94% present" with a weekly presence grid (colored dots per day)
4. **Dashboard overview screen (parent):** Landing page after login shows: GPA card, Unread Messages card, Recent Activities card, Next Event card -- a command center
5. **Teacher home screen:** Shows student profile (photo placeholder, name, grade) and quick-action buttons (Message Parent, Update Grade, Post Announcement)
6. **"Last updated" timestamps** on every data card so real-time polling is perceptible
7. **Responsive mobile layout** (sidebar collapses to bottom tab bar below 768px)
8. **Smooth CSS transitions** on card hover, message send animation, grade save confirmation toast
9. **Empty states** with friendly illustrations (SVG inline) when inbox is empty or no activities
10. **PHP production note modal:** A small dismissable "About this demo" info bar at top that explains the demo runs on a modern JS stack for fast prototype iteration, and maps 1:1 to a PHP/Laravel production build

