## 7. Backend Blueprint Detail

**File:** `mw-backend/edtech_blueprint.py`
**Blueprint prefix:** `/api/edtech`

### Tables (auto-created on first request if not exist)
```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS edtech_users (
  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
  email TEXT UNIQUE,
  password_hash TEXT,
  role TEXT,  -- 'parent' or 'teacher'
  name TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS edtech_messages (
  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
  from_user_id INTEGER,
  to_user_id INTEGER,
  body TEXT,
  is_read INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  created_at TEXT DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS edtech_grades (
  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
  student_name TEXT,
  subject TEXT,
  letter_grade TEXT,
  numeric_score INTEGER,
  updated_by INTEGER,
  updated_at TEXT DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS edtech_activities (
  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
  title TEXT,
  body TEXT,
  category TEXT,
  posted_by_name TEXT,
  created_at TEXT DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);
```

### Seed data (auto-seeded on first request)
- 2 users: parent + teacher (bcrypt hashed)
- 6 grade rows (Math A/95, English B+/88, Science A-/91, History B/84, Art A/97, PE A+/100)
- 4 activity items (grade milestone, science fair, attendance note, field trip)
- 2 seed messages (teacher introduces self, parent replies asking about homework)

### Endpoints

| Method | Path                          | Auth        | Description                              |
|--------|-------------------------------|-------------|------------------------------------------|
| POST   | /api/edtech/login             | none        | Returns JWT with role + name             |
| GET    | /api/edtech/messages          | JWT (any)   | Returns thread for current user's convo  |
| POST   | /api/edtech/messages          | JWT (any)   | Send a message to the other party        |
| PATCH  | /api/edtech/messages/:id/read | JWT (any)   | Mark message as read                     |
| GET    | /api/edtech/messages/unread   | JWT (any)   | Returns { count: N }                     |
| GET    | /api/edtech/performance       | JWT (any)   | Returns all grade rows for Alex          |
| POST   | /api/edtech/performance       | JWT teacher | Update one subject grade                 |
| GET    | /api/edtech/activities        | JWT (any)   | Returns all activity items, newest first |
| POST   | /api/edtech/activities        | JWT teacher | Create a new announcement                |
| GET    | /api/edtech/health            | none        | Returns { status: ok } (for deploy test) |

### JWT
- Use PyJWT (already installed on mw-backend)
- Secret: a hardcoded demo secret in the blueprint (`EDTECH_JWT_SECRET = "edtech-demo-2026"`)
- Token payload: `{ user_id, role, name, exp }`
- Expiry: 24 hours

