## 11. Scope Fences (what is explicitly OUT)

- No multi-student support (one seeded student is enough to prove the concept)
- No file upload / document sharing
- No push notifications (polling is sufficient to demonstrate real-time)
- No class roster beyond the single seeded student
- No gradebook history charts over multiple terms (single-term snapshot only)
- No parent self-registration (seeded logins only)
- No admin role (teacher is the highest role in this demo)
- No email/SMS integration
- No school branding customization UI

---

## 12. Production PHP Mapping (for cover letter / proposal)

The demo architecture maps cleanly to a PHP/Laravel production build:

| Demo layer           | PHP/Laravel equivalent              |
|----------------------|-------------------------------------|
| Flask blueprint      | Laravel Controller + Routes         |
| SQLite tables        | MySQL/PostgreSQL with Eloquent ORM  |
| JWT (PyJWT)          | Laravel Sanctum or Passport         |
| Vanilla JS frontend  | Vue.js or Livewire (or keep vanilla)|
| Polling (4s)         | Laravel Echo + Pusher for WebSockets|
| Static deploy        | Laravel on shared hosting or VPS    |

The front end, all user flows, and all data models remain identical. Only the runtime changes.

