## 13. Build Order for demo-builder

1. Create `edtech_blueprint.py` in mw-backend (tables + seed + all endpoints)
2. Register blueprint in `server.py`
3. Build `index.html` + `styles.css` (design system first)
4. Build `api.js` (all backend calls, auth header injection)
5. Build `app.js` (router, auth state, polling manager)
6. Build `login.js` (dual-role tiles)
7. Build `parent-home.js` + `teacher-home.js` (dashboard overviews)
8. Build `messages.js` (threaded messaging)
9. Build `performance.js` (gradebook + Chart.js)
10. Build `activities.js` (feed + compose)
11. Update `workSamples.js` registry entry
12. Smoke-test: open locally, log in as both roles, complete the reviewer walkthrough above

